body:
[Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=8615db4e00b2b417d3041b1caa27acb7)
```rust
pub struct S<'t>(usize, &'t str);

impl<'t> S<'t> {
    // error[E0700]: hidden type for `impl Trait` captures lifetime that does not appear in bounds
    pub fn foo<'s>(&'s mut self) -> impl FnMut() + 's {
        move || self.0 += 1
    }
}

fn main() {
    let mut s = S(0, "hello");
    s.foo()();
    println!("{}", s.0);
}
```

The `self: &'s mut S<'t>` implies `'t: 's`, so the signature should be correct. But compiler still complain that `'t` is captured but does not appear in `impl` bounds.

I checked the [error description of `E0700`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0700) and tried `impl FnMut() + 's where 't: 's` and `impl FnMut() + 's + 't`, while it still fails.

Note that when using `dyn Trait` as `pub fn foo<'s>(&'s mut self) -> Box<dyn FnMut() + 's>`, it compiles.
